  "Position and velocity are the same function": "",
  "Position equals velocity times time only": "",
  "Since velocity is the derivative of position (v = ds/dt), position is the antiderivative of velocity: s(t) = integral of v(t) dt + C. The constant C is determined by the initial position.": "",
  "What is the 'velocity from acceleration' relationship?": "",
