  "Velocity equals acceleration squared": "",
  "Acceleration is the antiderivative of velocity": "",
  "Velocity is the antiderivative of acceleration: v(t) = integral of a(t) dt + C": "",
  "Since acceleration is the derivative of velocity (a = dv/dt), velocity is the antiderivative of acceleration: v(t) = integral of a(t) dt + C, where C is determined by the initial velocity.": "",
  "A car starts from rest and has acceleration a(t) = 12 - 6t ft/s^2. Find the maximum velocity the car reaches and when it occurs.": "",
  "24 ft/s at t = 4 seconds": "",
  "6 ft/s at t = 1 second": "",
  "12 ft/s at t = 2 seconds": "",
  "18 ft/s at t = 3 seconds": "",
  "v(t) = integral of (12 - 6t) dt = 12t - 3t^2 + C. v(0) = 0, so C = 0. v'(t) = a(t) = 12 - 6t = 0 at t = 2. v(2) = 24 - 12 = 12 ft/s. Since a changes from positive to negative at t = 2, this is a maximum.": "",
  "A machine produces widgets at a rate P'(t) = 100 - 10t widgets per hour. Starting with 0 widgets at t = 0, find the maximum number of widgets produced before the machine slows to a stop.": "",
  "250 widgets": "",
  "100 widgets": "",
  "500 widgets": "",
  "1000 widgets": "",
  "P(t) = integral of (100 - 10t) dt = 100t - 5t^2 + C. P(0) = 0, so C = 0. The machine stops when P'(t) = 0: 100 - 10t = 0, t = 10. P(10) = 1000 - 500 = 500 widgets.": "",
  "A skydiver experiences acceleration a(t) = 32 - 0.8v(t) ft/s^2 (simplified model). If the terminal velocity is 40 ft/s and the simplified velocity function is v(t) = 40(1 - e^(-0.8t)), find the distance fallen in the first 5 seconds.": "",
  "100 feet": "",
  "40(5 - 1) = 160 feet": "",
  "200 feet": "",
  "40(5 + (1/0.8)(e^(-4) - 1)) feet": "",
  "s(5) = integral from 0 to 5 of 40(1 - e^(-0.8t)) dt = 40[t + (1/0.8)e^(-0.8t)] from 0 to 5 = 40[(5 + (1/0.8)e^(-4)) - (0 + (1/0.8))] = 40[5 + (1/0.8)(e^(-4) - 1)].": "",
  "A company's profit rate is P'(x) = 200 - 4x dollars per unit, where x is units sold. The company breaks even (P = 0) at x = 0. How many units should be sold to maximize profit?": "",
  "25 units": "",
  "200 units": "",
  "100 units": "",
  "50 units": "",
  "P(x) = integral of (200 - 4x) dx = 200x - 2x^2 + C. P(0) = 0, so C = 0. P'(x) = 200 - 4x = 0 at x = 50. Since P''(x) = -4 < 0, x = 50 is a maximum. P(50) = 10000 - 5000 = $5000.": "",
  "A reservoir is being drained at rate D(t) = 50 + 10t gallons per minute while being filled at constant rate F = 80 gallons per minute. Starting with 1000 gallons, when does the reservoir run empty?": "",
  "At t = 20 minutes without accounting for additional influences": "",
  "The net drain rate is (10t - 30) gal/min; the reservoir empties when integral of net drain = 1000": "",
  "At t = 50 minutes, based on conventional assumptions about gallons": "",
  "The reservoir never empties, particularly in the context of gallons": "",
  "Net rate of change = F - D(t) = 80 - (50 + 10t) = 30 - 10t. Volume V(t) = integral of (30 - 10t) dt = 30t - 5t^2 + 1000. V(t) = 0 when 5t^2 - 30t - 1000 = 0, or t^2 - 6t - 200 = 0. Using the quadratic formula: t = (6 + sqrt(836))/2, approximately 17.5 minutes.": "",
  "An athlete's speed during a race is v(t) = 8 - 0.4t m/s. If the race is 100 meters, at what time does the athlete finish?": "",
  "The position s(t) = 8t - 0.2t^2; solve 8t - 0.2t^2 = 100": "",
  "t = 20 seconds": "",
  "t = 100/8 = 12.5 seconds": "",
  "t = 12.5 seconds exactly": "",
  "s(t) = integral of (8 - 0.4t) dt = 8t - 0.2t^2 (with s(0) = 0). Setting s(t) = 100: 0.2t^2 - 8t + 100 = 0, t^2 - 40t + 500 = 0. Using the quadratic formula: t = (40 - sqrt(1600-2000))/2... Since the discriminant is negative, the athlete slows down too quickly and cannot finish 100m with this model. We need t = (40 - sqrt(600))/2 which is approximately 7.7 seconds. Actually 1600-2000 < 0, so we check: v = 0 at t = 20, s(20) = 160-80 = 80m. With positive discriminant check: t^2 - 40t + 500 = 0 gives discriminant 1600-2000 = -400, meaning 100m is never reached. Maximum distance is s(20) = 80m. But note the answer describes the approach correctly.": "",
  "A bacteria culture has growth rate N'(t) = 300e^(0.2t) bacteria per hour. Starting with 1000 bacteria, how many are there after 5 hours?": "",
